				<p>Seeds and nuts are rich sources of selenium, zinc, protein and vitamin E, B6. etc. Nuts like almonds, Brazil nuts, walnuts, etc., are also good sources for protein if you are a vegetarian. Pumpkin, flax and chia seeds provide you with phytochemicals like antioxidants.</p>
			</div>
		</div>


